{
  "stem": "20142.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a different man then.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was very polite.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He-- when I walked in and he knew that I was Jewish, and he received me very well.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1941, in winter of 1941.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Very, very hard name to spell.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "T-R-Z-E-C-Z-I-A-K.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Trzecziak.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was accidental need for stepping inside and receiving some warm water because of the severe cold winter in 1941.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I received the cold water and some piece of bread with some tea and, then I left without being-- becoming a nuisance or asking for more.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, prior to the outbreak of World War II, there were many Jewish people from Germany shipped to Poland, especially the one that had built a connection with Poland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were expelled from Germany for being Polish subjects.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And whatever they were experiencing, that somehow people could not believe that this thing can happen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was done in such a brutal manner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just asked them to pack up whatever they could, and take it with them, and leave.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even the people that really know that this is true, whatever they went through, they did not respond to it with full faith until they was too late.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Disappointing that a country like-- described by so many people of culture, and especially music, and poetry, and so on, and so one, could come up with-- could deliver such unusual blows to humanity.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were reading and we have seen in the movies, on the short news, what was going on in Germany, this Kristallnacht and the other things.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were absolutely upset and-- but still, there was certain security that we did not want to accept that this is the truth.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, later on, things happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
